choices.text:
{
    "name": "Carrot Pie Without Walnuts",
    "ingredients": [
        "1/2 cup butter",
        "1/2 cup white sugar",
        "2 eggs",
        "1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon",
        "1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg",
        "1/4 teaspoon ground allspice",
        "1/4 teaspoon ground ginger",
        "1/2 teaspoon salt",
        "1/2 cup all-purpose flour",
        "2 cups grated carrots",
        "1/2 cup raisins",
        "1/2 cup chopped dates",
        "1/2 cup chopped apples"
    ],
    "instructions": [
        "Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).",
        "In a medium bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.",
        "Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, ginger and salt.",
        "Stir in the flour, then fold in the carrots, raisins, dates and apples.",
        "Pour the mixture into a 9 inch pie pan.",
        "Bake in preheated oven for 40 minutes, or until a knife inserted into the center of the pie comes out clean."
    ]
}
